\section*{Problems associated with secondary data}
- The major problem with secondary data is that it has not been collected specifically for the purpose required. This means that if we are to use it, must check to ensure we understand what the figures collected represent, that is the population we are investigating the figure to the accuracy we require and finally the trustworthiness of the figures.
- Is the information actual, seasonal, adjusted, estimated or projected?
- The reason for collecting the data maybe unknown.
