These are persons attending as non-resident patients for investigations, therapeutic tests, operative procedure or other Rx and who requires some form of preparation period of recovery or both involving the provision of accommodation and other services.

\section*{14. Census}

A count of in-patients at a given time. The census is always taken in a hospital at the same time each day, usually midnight. It provides the number of in-patients at census taking time.

