\section*{Dispersion}
- It's the extent of the scatteredness of items around a measure of central tendency.
- The degree to which numerical data tend to spread about an average value is called the variation or dispersion of the data.
- A measure of dispersion indicates the extent to which the individual observes differ on average from the mean or from any other measure of central tendency.

\section*{Significance of measuring dispersion}
